Sorry uploader for saying this, but I totally hate when I find an incomplete DVD. Those bonus parts are very important, there you can find valuable informations about the movie and so on. 
The quality of the film is very bad, so for those who seek crisp and clear images, search for a blueray, becouse you'll be disappointed by this one.

Well, having reviewed this download I'm a little disappointed there is no DVD menu or information. The Quality is fine, it isn't great but it's not very good on a 1080p monitor. Another thing is that I believe the film is supposed to have a bit of a grain to it. As for the movie itself, it's flawless, one of the best ever made and in my top 10.
